    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-05-04T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-05-04T09:00:00-05:00" n="161"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d161">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/9839</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PTN1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-05-04T16:00:00+02:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 4, 1918, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received May 5, 2.57 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1248 [<hi rend="italic">1579</hi>]. Your 1248, May 3, 4 p.m. Took up matter
                    immediately and confidentially with <persName corresp="#p_SBS1">Baron
                        Sonnino</persName> who thinks that such a declaration will serve most useful
                    purpose and have an important effect. It will shake up Turkey and Bulgaria, and
                    will prove a <pb facs="0318" n="226" xml:id="pg_226"/> material aid against
                    Austria and also Germany. He expressed himself as very confident of the material
                    aid which the declaration would render to the Allied cause.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PTN1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nelson Page</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
